title: Snub icosidodecadodecahedron
summary: In geometry, the snub icosidodecadodecahedron is a nonconvex uniform polyhedron, indexed as U46. It has 104 faces (80 triangles, 12 pentagons, and 12 pentagrams), 180 edges, and 60 vertices.[1] As the name indicates, it belongs to the family of snub polyhedra.
